#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an7.62"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.62:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.62:0.2"
msgid "6. Abyākatavagga "
msgstr "6. The Undeclared Points "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 62. Mettasutta → māpuññabhāyisuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an7.62:0.3"
msgid "62. Mettasutta "
msgstr "62. Don’t Fear Good Deeds "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.89, sc1
msgctxt "an7.62:1.1"
msgid "“Mā, bhikkhave, puññānaṃ bhāyittha. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, don’t fear good deeds. "

#. VAR: yadidaṃ puññāni → yadidaṃ puññanti (bj) | yadidaṃ puññānanti (s1-3, pts1, c1)
msgctxt "an7.62:1.2"
msgid "Sukhassetaṃ, bhikkhave, adhivacanaṃ yadidaṃ puññāni. "
msgstr "For ‘good deeds’ is a term for happiness. "

#. VAR: bhikkhave, dīgharattaṃ katānaṃ puññānaṃ dīgharattaṃ iṭṭhaṃ → bhikkhave dīgharattaṃ iṭṭhaṃ (syā2, syā3), bhikkhave dīgharattaṃ puññānaṃ iṭṭhaṃ (?)
msgctxt "an7.62:1.3"
msgid "Abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, dīgharattaṃ katānaṃ puññānaṃ dīgharattaṃ iṭṭhaṃ kantaṃ manāpaṃ vipākaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ. "
msgstr "I recall undergoing for a long time the likable, desirable, and agreeable results of good deeds performed over a long time. "

#. VAR: mettacittaṃ → mettaṃ cittaṃ (bj, c1)
msgctxt "an7.62:1.4"
msgid "Satta vassāni mettacittaṃ bhāvesiṃ. "
msgstr "I developed a mind of love for seven years. "

#. VAR: mettacittaṃ → mettaṃ cittaṃ (bj, c1)
msgctxt "an7.62:1.5"
msgid "Satta vassāni mettacittaṃ bhāvetvā satta saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe nayimaṃ lokaṃ punāgamāsiṃ. "
msgstr "As a result, for seven eons of the cosmos contracting and expanding I didn’t return to this world again. "

#. VAR: Saṃvaṭṭamāne sudāhaṃ → saṃvaṭṭamānassudāhaṃ (bj, mr)
msgctxt "an7.62:1.6"
msgid "Saṃvaṭṭamāne sudāhaṃ, bhikkhave, loke ābhassarūpago homi, "
msgstr "As the cosmos contracted I went to the realm of streaming radiance. "

msgctxt "an7.62:1.7"
msgid "vivaṭṭamāne loke suññaṃ brahmavimānaṃ upapajjāmi. "
msgstr "As it expanded I was reborn in an empty mansion of Brahmā. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an7.62:2.1"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, brahmā homi mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso vasavattī. "
msgstr "There I was Brahmā, the Great Brahmā, the undefeated, the champion, the universal seer, the wielder of power. "

msgctxt "an7.62:2.2"
msgid "Chattiṃsakkhattuṃ kho panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sakko ahosiṃ devānamindo; "
msgstr "I was Sakka, lord of gods, thirty-six times. "

msgctxt "an7.62:2.3"
msgid "anekasatakkhattuṃ rājā ahosiṃ cakkavattī dhammiko dhammarājā cāturanto vijitāvī janapadatthāvariyappatto sattaratanasamannāgato. "
msgstr "Many hundreds of times I was a king, a wheel-turning monarch, a just and principled king. My dominion extended to all four sides, I achieved stability in the country, and I possessed the seven treasures. "

msgctxt "an7.62:2.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, imāni satta ratanāni ahesuṃ, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "These were my seven treasures: "

msgctxt "an7.62:2.5"
msgid "cakkaratanaṃ, hatthiratanaṃ, assaratanaṃ, maṇiratanaṃ, itthiratanaṃ, gahapatiratanaṃ, pariṇāyakaratanameva sattamaṃ. "
msgstr "the wheel, the elephant, the horse, the jewel, the woman, the treasurer, and the counselor as the seventh treasure. "

msgctxt "an7.62:2.6"
msgid "Parosahassaṃ kho pana me, bhikkhave, puttā ahesuṃ sūrā vīraṅgarūpā parasenappamaddanā. "
msgstr "I had over a thousand sons who were valiant and heroic, crushing the armies of my enemies. "

#. VAR: ajjhāvasinti → ajjhāvasati (si, mr) | ajjhāvasanti (s1, s2, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.62:2.7"
msgid "So imaṃ pathaviṃ sāgarapariyantaṃ adaṇḍena asatthena dhammena abhivijiya ajjhāvasinti. "
msgstr "After conquering this land girt by sea, I reigned by principle, without rod or sword. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.90, sc3
msgctxt "an7.62:3.1"
msgid "Passa puññānaṃ vipākaṃ, "
msgstr "See the result of good deeds, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: sukhesino → sukhesinaṃ (si, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.62:3.2"
msgid "Kusalānaṃ sukhesino; "
msgstr "of skillful deeds, for one seeking happiness. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:3.3"
msgid "Mettaṃ cittaṃ vibhāvetvā, "
msgstr "I developed a mind of love "

# NOTE: Note the very unusual use of bhikkhavo outside of introduction. Even though it is a variant, still as verse it makes sense.
#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: bhikkhavo → bhikkhave (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an7.62:3.4"
msgid "Satta vassāni bhikkhavo; "
msgstr "for seven years, mendicants. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:3.5"
msgid "Sattasaṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe, "
msgstr "For seven eons of expansion and contraction "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: punāgamiṃ → punāgamaṃ (bj, s1, s2, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.62:3.6"
msgid "Nayimaṃ lokaṃ punāgamiṃ. "
msgstr "I didn’t return to this world again. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an7.62:4.1"
msgid "Saṃvaṭṭamāne lokamhi, "
msgstr "As the world contracted "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:4.2"
msgid "homi ābhassarūpago; "
msgstr "I went to the realm of streaming radiance. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:4.3"
msgid "Vivaṭṭamāne lokasmiṃ, "
msgstr "And when it expanded "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:4.4"
msgid "suññabrahmūpago ahuṃ. "
msgstr "I went to an empty mansion of Brahmā. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an7.62:5.1"
msgid "Sattakkhattuṃ mahābrahmā, "
msgstr "Seven times I was a Great Brahmā, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:5.2"
msgid "vasavattī tadā ahuṃ; "
msgstr "and at that time I was the wielder of power. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:5.3"
msgid "Chattiṃsakkhattuṃ devindo, "
msgstr "Thirty-six times I was lord of gods, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:5.4"
msgid "devarajjamakārayiṃ. "
msgstr "acting as ruler of the gods. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an7.62:6.1"
msgid "Cakkavattī ahuṃ rājā, "
msgstr "Then I was king, a wheel-turning monarch, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: jambumaṇḍassa → jambudīpassa (bj) | jambūsaṇḍassa (s1-3) | jambusaṇḍassa (pts1)
msgctxt "an7.62:6.2"
msgid "jambumaṇḍassa issaro; "
msgstr "ruler of all India. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Muddhāvasitto → muddhābhisitto (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an7.62:6.3"
msgid "Muddhāvasitto khattiyo, "
msgstr "An anointed aristocrat, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:6.4"
msgid "manussādhipatī ahuṃ. "
msgstr "I was sovereign of all humans. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an7.62:7.1"
msgid "Adaṇḍena asatthena, "
msgstr "Without rod or sword, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:7.2"
msgid "vijeyya pathaviṃ imaṃ; "
msgstr "I conquered this land. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: kammena → dhammena (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.62:7.3"
msgid "Asāhasena kammena, "
msgstr "Through non-violent action "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:7.4"
msgid "samena manusāsi taṃ. "
msgstr "I guided it justly. "

# NOTE: I think BB has mistaken the tenses here: this should introduce the next section.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an7.62:8.1"
msgid "Dhammena rajjaṃ kāretvā, "
msgstr "After ruling this territory "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:8.2"
msgid "asmiṃ pathavimaṇḍale; "
msgstr "by means of principle, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:8.3"
msgid "Mahaddhane mahābhoge, "
msgstr "I was born in a rich family, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:8.4"
msgid "aḍḍhe ajāyihaṃ kule. "
msgstr "affluent and wealthy. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
#. VAR: sampanne → sampanno (bj) | sampuṇṇe (mr)
msgctxt "an7.62:9.1"
msgid "Sabbakāmehi sampanne, "
msgstr "It was replete with all sense pleasures, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:9.2"
msgid "ratanehi ca sattahi; "
msgstr "and the seven treasures. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:9.3"
msgid "Buddhā saṅgāhakā loke, "
msgstr "This was well taught by the Buddhas, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:9.4"
msgid "tehi etaṃ sudesitaṃ. "
msgstr "who bring the world together. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an7.62:10.1"
msgid "Eso hetu mahantassa, "
msgstr "This is the cause of greatness "

# NOTE: See BB’s note for reading.
#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: pathabyo me na vipajjati → puthavyo yena vuccati (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.62:10.2"
msgid "pathabyo me na vipajjati; "
msgstr "by which one is called a lord of the land. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:10.3"
msgid "Pahūtavittūpakaraṇo, "
msgstr "I was a majestic king, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: hoti → homi (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.62:10.4"
msgid "rājā hoti patāpavā. "
msgstr "with lots of property and assets. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
#. VAR: hoti → homi (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.62:11.1"
msgid "Iddhimā yasavā hoti, "
msgstr "Successful and glorious, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: jambumaṇḍassa → jambusaṇḍassa (bj, pts1) | jambūsaṇḍassa (s1-3)
msgctxt "an7.62:11.2"
msgid "jambumaṇḍassa issaro; "
msgstr "I was lord of India. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:11.3"
msgid "Ko sutvā nappasīdeyya, "
msgstr "Who would not be inspired by this, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:11.4"
msgid "api kaṇhābhijātiyo. "
msgstr "even someone of dark birth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.91, sc12
#. VAR: attakāmena → atthakāmena (bj, s1, s2, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an7.62:12.1"
msgid "Tasmā hi attakāmena, "
msgstr "Therefore someone who loves themselves, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:12.2"
msgid "mahattamabhikaṅkhatā; "
msgstr "aspiring to transcendence, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:12.3"
msgid "Saddhammo garukātabbo, "
msgstr "should respect the true teaching, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an7.62:12.4"
msgid "saraṃ buddhānasāsanan”ti. "
msgstr "remembering the instructions of the Buddhas.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.62:12.5"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
